injury.description: Isaac (thigh) expects to be ready for the start of the 2023-24 campaign, Khobi Price of the Orlando Sentinel reports.
Reid and the Timberwolves agreed Sunday on a three-year, $42 million deal that includes a player option, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.
The Timberwolves are preparing for Clark (Achilles) to miss at least the first half of the 2023-24 season, Jace Frederick of the St. Paul Pioneer Press reports.
Anderson (eye) has been ruled out for Tuesday's Game 5 against the Nuggets.
Minnesota announced Monday that McDaniels fractured his third and fourth metacarpals in his right hand, has been placed in a cast and will be out indefinitely.
Jaquez (shoulder) has been ruled out for Sunday's Summer League game against Portland, Ira Winderman of the South Florida Sun Sentinel reports.
George (knee) said Monday in his latest episode of "Podcast P with Paul George" that he plans to resume working out next week, Law Murray of The Athletic reports.
Diabate agreed to a two-way contract with the Clippers on Monday, Michael Scotto of USA Today reports.
Brown didn't return to Sunday's 104-103 loss to the Lakers in the Las Vegas Summer League after exiting in the second quarter with an ankle injury, Tomer Azarly of ClutchPoints.com reports.

Clippers president of basketball operations Lawrence Frank announced Thursday that Leonard underwent a clean-up procedure on his right knee June 6 and is expected to be fully recovered for training camp, Law Murray of The Athletic reports.
McGruder (foot) will not play in Sunday's game against the Bulls.
Burks is expected to remain with the Pistons according to ESPN's Adrian Wojnarowski, as Detroit is planning to pick up his $10.5 million option for 2023-24.

Pistons head coach Dwane Casey acknowledged Tuesday that Diallo (ankle) likely won't be available to play again this season by the time he's re-evaluated in 3-to-4 weeks, Omari Sankofa II of the Detroit Free Press reports.
Krejci (ankle) has been ruled out for the remainder of Sunday's matchup with Dallas, Brad Rowland of the Locked On Podcast Network reports.
Koloko won't play in any of Toronto's Summer League games due to a respiratory condition, Vivek Jacob of the Raptors' official site reports.
Porter (foot) exercised his $6.3 million player option for the 2023-24 campaign Tuesday, Shams Charania of The Athletic reports.
Dowtin (ankle) signed a training camp deal with the Raptors on Saturday, Shams Charania of The Athletic reports.
The Raptors signed Harper (shoulder) to a two-way contract Thursday, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.
Baldwin won't play in Saturday's Summer League game against Chicago, Josh Robbins of The Athletic reports.
The Wizards signed Omoruyi (ankle) to a two-way contract Tuesday, Josh Robbins of The Athletic reports.
Cooks will miss Saturday's Summer League game against the Bulls for an undisclosed reason, Josh Robbins of The Athletic reports.
Davis (undisclosed) has been ruled out for Saturday's Summer League game against the Bulls,Josh Robbins of The Athletic reports.
Gallinari was traded to the Wizards as part of a three-team trade surrounding Kristaps Porzingis, Marcus Smart and Tyus Jones. Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.
Coulibaly is out for Saturday's game versus the Bulls due to an undisclosed reason, Josh Robbins of The Athletic reports.
Rollins (undisclosed) won't play in Saturday's Summer League game against the Bulls, Josh Robbins of The Athletic reports.
Goodwin (knee) won't play in Saturday's Summer League game against the Grizzlies, Duane Rankin of The Arizona Republic reports.
The Suns are moving forward with the plan of keeping Ayton (ribs) to play alongside Devin Booker, Kevin Durant and Bradley Beal, Chris Haynes of Turner Sports reports.
Collins (finger) underwent surgery on April 8 to address an infection in his finger,  Tom Orsborn of the San Antonio Express-News reports.

Bassey is likely out for the rest of the 2022-23 campaign after the Spurs confirmed Wednesday that the big man suffered a non-displaced fracture of his left patella, Tom Osborn of the San Antonio Express-News reports.
Lewis (ankle) will be on a two-way contract with the Bulls in 2023-24, Will Gottlieb of AllCHGO.com reports.
Bulls vice president of basketball operations Arturas Karnisovas said Friday that he does not anticipate Ball (knee) playing during the 2023-24 season,  Jamal Collier of ESPN reports.
Rozier (foot) is out Sunday against the Cavaliers.
Martin (knee) does not have a timetable, but his knee is improving according to Rod Boone of The Charlotte Observer.
Washington (foot) is out for Sunday's tilt against the Cavaliers.
Smith is unavailable for Saturday's Summer League game against the Timberwolves, Sam Perley of the Hornets' official site reports.
Williams underwent successful surgery on a torn ligament located in his right thumb on Wednesday.
Oubre (shoulder) will not play in Sunday's finale against the Cavaliers.

Alvarado (leg) has been cleared to resume on-court activities, but he won't suit up for Wednesday's Play-In matchup against the Thunder and isn't expected to resume game action for at least one more week, Andrew Lopez of ESPN.com reports.
McCollum underwent surgery to repair a torn UCL in his right thumb Tuesday.

Pelicans executive David Griffin said Friday that Williamson (hamstring) was never cleared for 5-on-5 or even full-court 3-on-3 work before the Pelicans' Play-In Matchup against the Thunder, Andrew Lopez of ESPN.com reports.
Ellis won't play in Saturday's Summer League game against Milwaukee due to an undisclosed reason, Jason Anderson of The Sacramento Bee reports.
Dellavedova underwent surgery to repair the fractured index finger on his right hand Wednesday and he's currently without a timetable to return, Jason Anderson of The Sacramento Bee reports.
Queta (foot) will miss the remainder of the Summer League, Jason Anderson of The Sacramento Beereports.
Sabonis (thumb) re-negotiated his contract with the Kings on Saturday and has now agreed to an extension worth $217 million over five years, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.
Jones (undisclosed) won't play in Saturday's Summer League game against the Bucks, Jason Anderson of The Sacramento Bee reports.
Wright (ankle) will miss the remainder of the Summer League.
The Mavericks signed Williams (hand) to a four-year, $54 million contract after acquiring him in a three-team sign-and-trade with the Celtics and Spurs, Shams Charania of The Athletic reports.
Hardy will miss the remainder of the 2023 Summer League due to a left shoulder contusion, NBA writer Marc Stein reports.
Tate (knee) has been ruled out of Sunday's game against the Wizards.
An MRI revealed a Grade 2 ankle sprain in Thompson's left ankle an will be out 2-3 weeks, Marc J. Spears of ESPN.com reports.
Whitehead (foot) was selected by the Nets with the No. 22 pick in the 2023 NBA Draft.
The Nets agreed to sign Smith (toe) to a one-year contract Saturday, Shams Charania of The Athletic reports.

Finney-Smith underwent a procedure Wednesday to correct a fracture of the right fifth finger but is expected to be cleared for offseason workouts in six weeks, Ian Begley of SportsNet New York reports
Sims underwent season-ending surgery on his right shoulder Wednesday, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.
Quickley (ankle) has been ruled out for Friday's Game 6 versus Miami, Anthony Chiang of the Miami Herald reports.
Randle has undergone arthroscopic surgery on his left ankle and is  not expected to resume basketball activities later this summer, Steve Popper of Newsday reports.
The Knicks signed Windler (foot) to a two-way contract Monday, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.
Samanic (back) has been ruled out for Sunday's Summer League game versus the Rockets, Tony Jones of The Athletic reports.
Sensabaugh (knee) has been ruled out for Sunday's Summer League game against the Rockets.
Agbaji (back) has been ruled out for Sunday's Summer League game against the Rockets.
Juzang (quadriceps) signed a two-way contract with the Jazz on Wednesday, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.
Hendricks (hamstring) has been ruled out for Sunday's Summer League game against the Rockets.
An MRI done on Thursday revealed that George has a lateral sprain on his right ankle, Eric Walden of The Salt Lake Tribune reports.
Kessler (concussion) has been ruled out for the remainder of the regular season, Tony Jones of The Athletic reports.
Mann suffered a small avulsion fracture in his right middle finger and is expected to return to basketball activities in two weeks, Joe Mussatto of The Oklahoman reports.
Williams (wrist) underwent a successful planned procedure Tuesday to remove hardware from his initial surgery, Clemente Almanza of USA Today reports.
Pokusesvki hasn't received medical permission to train until August, ruling him out for the FIBA World Cup, Eurohoops.net reports.
Oladipo was traded to the Thunder on Friday, Shams Charania of The Athletic reports.
Winslow underwent successful left ankle surgery Wednesday and is anticipated to be ready for the 2023-24 season.
Henderson (shoulder) is out for Tuesday's Summer League game against the Hornets, Sam Perley of the Hornets' official site reports.
The Trail Blazers said Thursday that Little underwent a core muscle surgery on his left side, Sean Highkin of RoseGardenReport.com reports.
Johnson dislocated his right finger during Friday's Summer League game against Houston and will miss the rest of the tournament, Jason Quick of The Athletic reports.
Antetokounmpo underwent a cleanup procedure on his knee in late June and is uncertain for FIBA World Cup play in August, Shams Charania of The Athletic reports.
Middleton underwent a surgical procedure on his right knee shortly after the Bucks lost to Heat in the first round of the playoffs in late April, Tim Bontemps of ESPN.com reports.
Iguodala (wrist surgery) has been  cleared to intensify on-court workouts and should return to practice in about a week.
Bane agreed to a five-year, $207 million contract extension with the Grizzlies on Friday, ESPN's Adrian Wojnarowski reports.
Kennard (shoulder) has been ruled out for Game 6 versus the Lakers on Friday.
Clarke suffered a season-ending left Achilles tear during Friday's loss to the Nuggets, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.
Adams (knee) will likely be sidelined throughout the entirety of the postseason, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.
Hood-Schifino (groin) will not play in Sunday's Summer League matchup against the Clippers, Mike Trudell of Spectrum SportsNet reports.
Christie (hip) is ruled out for Sunday's Summer League matchup with the Clippers, Mike Trudell of Spectrum SportsNet reports.
